{"parse":{"title":"meat","pageid":1746,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"{{also|méat}}\n==English==\n{{wp}}\n\n===Etymology===\n{{root|en|ine-pro|*meh₂d-|id=wet}}\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|mete}}, from {{inh|en|ang|mete||food}}, from {{inh|en|gmw-pro|*mati}}, from {{inh|en|gem-pro|*matiz|t=food}}, from {{der|en|ine-pro|*meh₂d-|id=wet|t=to drip, ooze; grease, fat}}. \n{{col-top|2|cog}}\nCognate with {{cog|frr|Miit|t=meat}}, {{cog|da|mad|t=food}}, {{cog|fo,is|matur|t=food, meal}}, {{cog|nrn|mader|t=food}}, {{cog|nb,nn,sv|mat|t=food}}, {{cog|got|𐌼𐌰𐍄𐍃|t=food}}.\n\nA ''-ja-'' derivation from the same base is found in {{cog|dum|-}} and {{cog|gml|met|t=lean pork}}, from which {{cog|nl|met|t=minced pork}} and {{cog|de|Mett|t=minced meat}} derive, respectively. Compare also {{cog|sga|mess|t=animal feed}} and {{cog|cy|mes|t=acorns}}, {{cog|en|mast|t=fodder for swine and other animals}}, which are probably from the same root.\n{{col-bottom}}\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{enPR|mēt}}, {{IPA|en|/miːt/}}\n* {{IPA|en|/mit/|a=GA}}\n* {{IPA|en|/miːʔ/|/miːh/|a=Dublin}}\n* {{audio|en|en-us-meat.ogg|a=US}}\n* {{audio|en|En-uk-meat.ogg|a=UK}}\n* {{audio|en|LL-Q1860 (eng)-Back ache-meat.wav}}\n* {{rhymes|en|iːt|s=1}}\n* {{homophones|en|meet|mete}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun|~}}\n\n# {{senseid|en|Q10990}} {{lb|en|uncountable}} The [[flesh]] (muscle tissue) of a killed [[animal]] used as [[food]], or a food designed to replicate its taste and texture (like plant-based meat). {{defdate|from 14th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|flesh|Thesaurus:meat}}\n#: {{hyper|en|food<id:Q2095>}}\n#: {{ant|en|drink}}\n#: {{ux|en|A large portion of domestic '''meat''' production comes from animals raised on factory farms.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The homesteading teenager shot a deer to supply his family with wild '''meat''' for the winter.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|title=The Book of Sharks|author={{w|Richard Ellis (biologist)|Richard Ellis}}|year=1983|publisher=Knopf|ISBN=0679722106|passage=In many parts of the world, shark '''meat''' is an acceptable and desirable form of protein.|page=144}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|date=2010-10-19|author=Andy Atkins|title=Debate on meat-eating does not cut the mustard|journal=w:The Guardian|passage=While people who eat no '''meat''' at all are identified and identifiable as vegetarians, there is no commonly accepted term for people who eat it only a couple of times a week and are selective about its quality.\n|url=https://www.theguardian.com/environment/cif-green/2010/oct/19/less-meat-debate}}\n# {{lb|en|countable}} A type of meat, by anatomic position and provenance. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The butchery's profit rate on various '''meats''' varies greatly.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|author=Seamus Bruner|title=Controligarchs: Exposing the Billionaire Class, Their Secret Deals, and the Globalist Plot to Dominate Your Life |year=2023|passage=It should come as no surprise that while the peasants are expected to eat fermented fungi, lab-grown '''meats''' and maggot milkshakes, the Controligarchs — with their private chefs — have no intention of doing the same.}}\n#* {{quote-journal|en|author=Madeline Holcombe|title=There is a link between the meat you eat and a chronic disease, according to new research|magazine=w:CNN|url=https://www.cnn.com/2024/08/20/health/meat-red-processed-diabetes-wellness/index.html|date=2024-08-20|passage=Regularly eating red and processed '''meats''' in particular is associated with a higher risk of type 2 diabetes, according to an analysis of data from 31 study cohorts published Tuesday in the journal The Lancet Diabetes & Endocrinology.}}\n# {{lb|en|now|archaic|dialectal}} {{U|food}}, for animals or humans, especially solid food. {{defdate|from 8th c.}}\n#: {{co|en|[[meat and drink|'''meat''' and drink]]}}\n#* {{RQ:Tyndale NT|Matthew|XXV|text=I was anhongred, and ye gave me '''meate'''. I thursted, and ye gave me drinke.}}\n#* {{RQ:Montaigne Florio Essayes|chapter=8|book=II|page=232|passage=And he was pleased to accompany them in their death; for, he pined away by abstaining from all manner of '''meat'''.}}\n#* {{RQ:Shakespeare Timon of Athens|text=Your greatest want is, you want much of '''meat''': / Why should you want? Behold, the Earth hath Rootes{{nb...}}.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1879|author=w:Silas Hocking|title={{w|Her Benny (novel)|Her Benny}}\n|passage=As full of fun and frolic as an egg is full of '''meat'''.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1936|author=w:Djuna Barnes|title=Nightwood|page=13|publisher=Faber & Faber|year_published=2007\n|passage=The way she said ‘dinner’ and the way she said ‘champagne’ gave '''meat''' and liquid their exact difference{{nb...}}.}}\n# {{lb|en|now|rare}} A type of food, a [[dish]]. {{defdate|from 9th c.}}\n# {{lb|en|archaic}} A [[meal]]. {{defdate|from 9th c.}}\n#* {{RQ:Tyndale NT|Matthew|8|text=And hit cam to passe, thatt Jesus satt at '''meate''' in his housse.}}\n# {{lb|en|obsolete}} {{U|meal}}; [[flour]].\n# {{lb|en|uncountable}} Any relatively thick, [[solid]] part of a [[fruit]], [[nut]] etc. {{defdate|from 15th c.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The apple looked fine on the outside, but the '''meat''' was not very firm.}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1954|author=Cothburn O'Neal|title=The Dark Lady|page=12\n|passage=She took her spoon and stirred the melted butter into the yellow '''meat''' of the yam.}}\n# {{senseid|en|penis}} {{lb|en|slang|vulgar}} A [[penis]]. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|Thesaurus:penis}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1993|author=Nancy Friday|title=Women on top: how real life has changed women's sexual fantasies|pageurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=2it03Dzk6dEC&pg=PA538&dq=fucked+me+with+his+big+meat&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ZfbvTr-iEIGwiQLgr5C1Dg&ved=0CFMQ6AEwBg|page=538\n|passage=He sits me on the floor (the shower is still beating down on us). He lays me down and slides his huge '''meat''' into me.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=John Patrick|title=Play Hard, Score Big|pageurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=Jyh_fpojTlsC&pg=PA54&dq=fucked+me+with+his+big+meat&hl=en&sa=X&ei=ZfbvTr-iEIGwiQLgr5C1Dg&ved=0CDsQ6AEwAg|page=54\n|passage=Just the tight, hot caress of his bowels surrounding my '''meat''' gave me pleasures I had only dreamed of before that day.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2011|author=Wade Wright|title=Two Straight Guys|pageurl=http://books.google.com/books?id=5pNiqJMQZxoC&pg=PA41&dq=%22face+fucking%22&hl=en&ei=Qi3DTveEN-LniALO3rXTCw&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=2&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAQ|page=41\n|passage=Both men were completely, and very actively into this face fucking! Suddenly Bill pulled off of Jim's '''meat''' and said,}}\n# {{lb|en|colloquial}} The [[best]] or most substantial part of something. {{defdate|from 16th c.}}\n#: {{syn|en|crux|gist|Thesaurus:gist}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1577|author=w:Gerald Eades Bentley|title=The Arte of Angling\n|passage={{...}}it is time to begin \"A Dialogue between Viator and Piscator,\" which is the '''meat''' of the matter.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2007|author=Robert Kenneth Jones|title=The Shudder Pulps|page=6\n|passage=The editor called the new \"novels\" book-lengthers without the trivialities and slow development of the usual novel. \"They have all the plot complications, '''meat''' and excitement that readers demand,\" he stated.}}\n# {{lb|en|sports}} The [[sweet spot]] of a [[bat]] or [[club]] (in cricket, golf, baseball etc.). {{defdate|from 20th c.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He hit it right on the '''meat''' of the bat.}}\n# {{lb|en|slang}} A [[meathead]].\n#: {{ux|en|Throw it in here, '''meat'''.}}\n# {{lb|en|Australian Aboriginal}} A [[totem]], or {{lb|en|by metonymy}} a [[clan]] or [[clansman]] which uses it.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1949|title=Oceania|author=Vol.XX\n|passage=When a stranger comes to an aboriginal camp or settlement in north-western NSW, he is asked by one of the older aborigines: \"What '''meat''' (clan) are you?\"}}\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=1973|author=M. Fennel; A. Grey|title=Nucoorilma\n|passage=Granny Sullivan was ‘dead against’ the match at first because they did not know \"what my '''meat''' was and because I was a bit on the fair side.\"}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1977|author=A. K. Eckermann|title=Group Organisation and Identity|passage=Some people maintained that she was \"sung\" because her family had killed or eaten the \"'''meat'''\" (totem) of another group.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1992|author=P. Taylor|title=Tell it Like it Is|passage=Our family{{...}}usually married the red kangaroo \"'''meat'''\".}}\n#* '''1993,''' J. Janson, ''Gunjies''\n#*: That’s a beautiful goanna.{{nb...}}. He’s my '''meat''', can’t eat him.\n\n====Usage notes====\n* The sense \"flesh of an animal used as food\" is often understood to exclude [[fish]] and other [[seafood]]. The exclusion of [[poultry]] from the category of meat has become outdated. <!--source: Chambers 1908-->\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|inmeats|all garnish and no meat\n|antimeat\n|Australian as a meat pie| meat hand\n|bakemeat\n|batmeat\n|bear meat\n|beat one's meat|advanced meat recovery|mechanically separated meat|wheat meat\n|beat the meat\n|bushmeat\n|bush meat\n|camel meat\n|cat meat\n|catmeat\n|cat's meat\n|chew the meat and spit out the bones\n|chicken's-meat\n|clean meat\n|cockmeat\n|coconut meat\n|cold meat\n|cold meat box\n|cold meat cart\n|cold meat train|lone-star-tick meat allergy|red meat allergy|tick meat allergy|tick-induced meat allergy\n|commodity meat\n|cow meat\n|crab meat\n|crabmeat\n|cuckoo's meat\n|cultured meat\n|dark meat|camp meat|meat off\n|dead meat\n|deer meat\n|deli meat\n|dog meat\n|don't get your meat where you get your bread\n|double-dead meat\n|duckmeat\n|ducksmeat\n|duck's-meat\n|easy meat\n|fancy meat\n|fleshmeat|all motion and no meat\n|forcemeat\n|fragrant meat\n|frankenmeat\n|fresh meat\n|fuck-meat\n|fuckmeat\n|girlmeat\n|goatmeat\n|ground meat\n|horsemeat\n|I don't eat meat\n|inmeat\n|kangaroo meat\n|light meat\n|loose-meat sandwich\n|luncheon meat\n|lunch meat\n|mad as a meat axe\n|make meat\n|mammalian meat allergy\n|man-meat\n|meat-and-potatoes\n|meat and potatoes\n|meat and three\n|meat and two veg\n|meat ant\n|meatarian\n|meat assault\n|meatatarian\n|meat ax\n|meat axe\n|meatbag\n|meatball\n|meat bee\n|meat biscuit\n|meatbot\n|meat box\n|meatcake\n|meatcase\n|meat-chopper\n|meat crayon\n|meat curtains\n|meat dealer\n|meat diaper\n|meat draw\n|meat-eater\n|meateater\n|meat eater\n|meat-eating\n|meated\n|meatface\n|meatfest\n|meat flaps\n|meat floss\n|meatfluencer\n|meat fly\n|meatfork\n|meatful\n|meat glue\n|meat grinder\n|meatgrinder\n|meathead\n|meatheaded\n|meat hook,meathook\n|meat house\n|meatilicious\n|meat injection\n|meat in the room\n|meatish\n|meat jelly\n|meat jun\n|meatless\n|meatlike\n|meat loaf\n|meatloaf\n|meat lovers'\n|meatman\n|meat market\n|meatness\n|meat offering\n|meat on one's bones\n|meat on the bones\n|meatpacker\n|meatpacking\n|meat pad\n|meat-pie\n|meat pie\n|meatpole\n|meat puppet\n|meatpuppet\n|meat rack\n|meat raffle\n|meat robot\n|meat rod\n|meat safe\n|meat-safe\n|meat-safe cot\n|meat sauce\n|meat scepter\n|meat sceptre\n|meat shield\n|meatshot\n|meat shot\n|meat-space\n|meat space\n|meatspace\n|meat stick\n|meatsuit\n|meat sweats\n|meat syringe\n|meat tea\n|meat thermometer\n|meat ticket\n|meat tray\n|meat wagon\n|meat-wagon\n|meatware\n|meat wool\n|meatworker\n|meatworks\n|meaty\n|meatza\n|meet-meat merger\n|milk before meat\n|minced meat\n|mock meat\n|monkey meat\n|more sauce than meat\n|mystery meat\n|mystery meat navigation\n|Natchitoches meat pie\n|nonmeat\n|noonmeat\n|nutmeat\n|one man's meat is another man's poison\n|piece of meat\n|pigmeat\n|plates of meat\n|processed meat\n|rapemeat\n|red meat\n|red meat radish\n|roast-meat clothes\n|room meat\n|rose meat\n|salt meat\n|sausage meat\n|sharkmeat\n|sheepmeat\n|sidemeat\n|smoked meat\n|smoke meat\n|snakemeat\n|sousemeat\n|soymeat\n|spoonmeat\n|spoon-meat\n|star meat\n|sweater meat\n|sweatmeat\n|sweetmeat\n|synthetic meat\n|the other white meat\n|think meat\n|tiger meat\n|variety meat\n|whalemeat\n|white meat\n|wildmeat\n}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|srn|meti}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|animal flesh used as food}}{{multitrans|data=\n* Abkhaz: {{tt|ab|ажьы}}\n* Afar: {{t|aa|cado}}\n* Afrikaans: {{tt+|af|vleis}}\n* Ahom: {{tt|aho|𑜃𑜢𑜤𑜰𑜫}}\n* Ai-Cham: {{tt|aih|naːn⁴}}\n* Ainu: {{tt|ain|カㇺ|tr=kam}}\n* Albanian: {{tt+|sq|mish}}\n* Amami Ōshima:\n*: Northern Amami Ōshima: {{tt|ryn|肉|tr=しし, shishi}}, {{tt|ryn|身|tr=みー, mī}}\n*: Southern Amami Ōshima: {{tt|ams|肉|tr=しし, shishi}}, {{tt|ams|身|tr=みー, mī}}\n* Amharic: {{tt|am|ሥጋ}}\n* Andi: {{tt|ani|рикьи}}\n* Ao: {{t|njo|shi}} {{q|Chungli}}\n* Arabic: {{tt|ar|لَحْم|m}}\n*: Egyptian Arabic: {{tt|arz|لحمة|f|tr=láḥma}}\n*: Iraqi Arabic: {{tt|acm|لحم|f|tr=laḥam}}\n*: South Levantine Arabic: {{tt|ajp|لحمة|f|tr=laḥme}}\n*: Yemeni Arabic: {{tt|ayn|شركة|f|tr=šerkeh}} {{q|Sanaa}}\n* Aramaic:\n*: Classical Syriac: {{tt|syc|ܒܣܪܐ|tr=besrā}}\n* Archi: {{tt|aqc|акь}}\n* Armenian: {{tt+|hy|միս}}\n* Aromanian: {{tt|rup|carne|f}}\n* Arrernte:\n*: Eastern Arrernte: {{t|aer|kere}}\n* Ashkun: {{tt|ask|mos}}\n* Assamese: {{tt|as|মাংস}}, {{tt|as|মঙহ}}\n* Asturian: {{tt+|ast|carne|f}}\n* Avar: {{tt|av|гьан}}\n* Azerbaijani: {{tt+|az|ət}}\n* Baluchi: {{tt|bal|گوشت|tr=gošt}}\n* Bangi: {{t|bni|mosuni}}\n* Bashkir: {{tt|ba|ит}}\n* Basque: {{tt|eu|haragi}}, {{tt|eu|okela}}\n* Bats: {{tt|bbl|დითხ}}, {{tt|bbl|დითხი̆}}\n* Beja: {{tt|bej|shaat}}\n* Belarusian: {{tt+|be|мя́са|n}}\n* Bengali: {{tt+|bn|মাংস}}, {{tt+|bn|গোশত}}\n* Bhojpuri: {{t|bho|मांस}}\n* Bikol:\n*: Central Bikol: {{tt+|bcl|karne}}\n* Boloki: {{t|bkt|nyama}}\n* Borôro: {{tt|bor|ködü}}\n* Bouyei: {{tt|pcc|noh}}\n* Breton: {{tt+|br|kig|m}}\n* Bulgarian: {{tt+|bg|месо́|n}}\n* Burmese: {{tt+|my|အသား}}, {{tt+|my|မံသ}}\n* Carpathian Rusyn: {{tt|rue|мнясо|n}}\n* Catalan: {{tt+|ca|carn|f}}\n* Cebuano: {{tt|ceb|unod}}, {{tt|ceb|karne}}\n* Central Atlas Tamazight: {{tt|tzm|ⴰⴽⵙⵓⵎ|m}}\n* Chadong: {{tt|cdy|naːn⁴}}\n* Cham:\n*: Eastern Cham: {{tt|cjm|ꨣꨯꨤꨱꨥ|tr=ralauw}}\n* Ch